WEBVTT

00:06.005 --> 00:06.923
[melancholy soul music]

00:07.007 --> 00:08.717
[man]  ♪ Hurtin', baby ♪

00:13.471 --> 00:16.224
♪ That's when my love left the story... ♪

00:17.892 --> 00:20.020
Hey, Reggie...

00:20.103 --> 00:22.522
[narrator]  Ah... the pity "hey."

00:22.605 --> 00:24.858
Lately,
Reggie Green's been inundated with them,

00:24.941 --> 00:26.735
as if he hadn't already
been through enough.

00:26.818 --> 00:29.946
Three weeks ago,
a house party comes to an end

00:30.030 --> 00:32.741
with Reggie staring down the barrel
of a gun,

00:32.824 --> 00:34.409
courtesy of a campus security guard.

00:34.492 --> 00:37.412
He needed to see some ID, he said.

00:37.495 --> 00:38.830
Watch closely.

00:38.913 --> 00:42.208
1825: in response to a slave revolt

00:42.292 --> 00:46.004
at a nearby Ivy,
Winchester issues arms to locals.

00:46.087 --> 00:49.883
Their goal-- to prevent the same from
happening in Winchester's hallowed halls,

00:49.966 --> 00:53.261
because bigots with guns
has never gone wrong.

00:53.803 --> 00:57.974
1930. Winchester makes
its campus security department official.

00:58.058 --> 01:01.061
The gun policy is not revisited.

01:02.312 --> 01:06.191
Freshman year. Though Howard University
was Reggie's first choice,

01:06.274 --> 01:09.319
Winchester's computer science program
was peerless.

01:09.819 --> 01:12.447
And upon finding a home
at Armstrong-Parker,

01:12.530 --> 01:15.533
Reggie is filled with hope.

01:15.617 --> 01:17.410
Hi. Mm-hmm.

01:19.079 --> 01:23.500
♪ Hurtin', hurtin', hurtin', hurtin'
Hurtin' ♪

01:23.583 --> 01:26.085
[rock music playing]

01:26.169 --> 01:28.213
Hey, Reggie.

01:28.296 --> 01:31.049
Again... Clifton,

01:31.132 --> 01:32.926
if you're gonna make Hot Pockets,

01:33.510 --> 01:34.969
open a window.

01:35.053 --> 01:38.181
This room smells like a pig died
in a Little Caesars.

01:38.264 --> 01:39.432
And headphones, man.

01:39.516 --> 01:41.309
What the fuck are you listening to?

01:41.392 --> 01:42.852
It's bomb, isn't it?

01:42.936 --> 01:45.313
I can gift you a copy on iTunes
if you want.

01:45.396 --> 01:46.731
I definitely do not want.

01:47.232 --> 01:50.276
I thought we agreed
this would be a dry room.

01:52.028 --> 01:55.031
Your side is dry. Mine is drowning.

01:58.535 --> 01:59.536
[music stops]

02:05.834 --> 02:09.045
Reggie, I know you've recently
gone through something traumatic.

02:09.129 --> 02:10.463
Yeah, this conversation.

02:10.547 --> 02:13.174
I can't imagine being pistol-whipped...

02:13.258 --> 02:14.092
-What?
-in front of--

02:14.175 --> 02:15.176
That's not what happened.

02:15.844 --> 02:17.387
I can be more than a roommate.

02:17.470 --> 02:19.848
I can be a consigliere,

02:19.931 --> 02:22.851
a shoulder on which to cry, or...

02:22.934 --> 02:25.103
dare I say, a friend?

02:25.186 --> 02:27.230
We organized a rally
around what went down,

02:27.313 --> 02:29.190
and you tried to cock-block us
with your own.

02:29.274 --> 02:31.317
Yeah, but I didn't know you then.

02:31.901 --> 02:32.944
Pain is pain.

02:33.027 --> 02:34.487
This isn't a competish, Reg.

02:34.571 --> 02:35.947
Don't shorten my name.

02:36.030 --> 02:41.744
Just know this room
is a safe space, Reginald.

02:42.495 --> 02:44.330
Don't lengthen my name, either.

02:45.456 --> 02:47.584
[cell phone chimes]

03:09.647 --> 03:10.857
Hey, Reggie.

03:11.524 --> 03:14.152
-Hey, man.
-[exhales]

03:15.737 --> 03:16.738
[Gabe] Everything okay?

03:17.739 --> 03:20.950
Yeah, uh... just caught me daydreaming.

03:22.535 --> 03:24.162
So did you get my text?

03:25.204 --> 03:27.248
It's not about the doc I'm making, really.

03:27.332 --> 03:28.750
I just want to sit down and talk.

03:28.833 --> 03:30.251
I'm good.

03:30.335 --> 03:31.377
I've moved on.

03:41.804 --> 03:44.349
I can handle A-P being integrated.

03:45.058 --> 03:46.935
I don't even have an issue
with white folks.

03:47.602 --> 03:50.396
Clifton's just... so white.

03:50.480 --> 03:54.108
Like, um, he calls his parents
by their first names.

03:54.192 --> 03:57.237
He's always asking me if I've heard
of Chance the Rapper.

03:57.320 --> 03:59.864
He doesn't even use a washcloth.

03:59.948 --> 04:01.115
How do you feel clean?

04:01.199 --> 04:02.200
Reggie.

04:02.283 --> 04:05.119
[sighs] Why are you here?

04:05.203 --> 04:07.997
So I won't be labeled the angry black man.

04:08.665 --> 04:11.876
We want to ensure you're dealing
with what happened in a healthy fashion.

04:11.960 --> 04:13.294
We care about you.

04:13.378 --> 04:15.296
[laughs]

04:15.380 --> 04:16.965
That the school's new motto?

04:17.548 --> 04:18.883
How do you say that in Latin?

04:18.967 --> 04:21.552
Non curo de te...

04:21.636 --> 04:22.929
If Winchester gave a shit about me,

04:23.012 --> 04:24.681
they wouldn't have just given me a shrink.

04:24.764 --> 04:26.724
They would've given
that motherfucker a shrink.

04:27.433 --> 04:31.729
They just covering they asses
in case somebody kills themselves.

04:32.063 --> 04:35.275
But-- well, you're not thinking
about killing yourself, though?

04:37.610 --> 04:40.571
[scoffs, chuckles]

04:41.489 --> 04:42.365
Hey, Reg...

04:42.448 --> 04:45.660
-Can you give these to Dean Fairbanks?
-You can give them to him yourself.

04:45.743 --> 04:47.495
He wants to see you.

04:47.578 --> 04:50.540
[Dean Fairbanks] So you just
quit the presidency in an email?

04:50.623 --> 04:52.125
Text message.

04:52.208 --> 04:56.087
Troy, don't you see?
You're playing right into their narrative.

04:56.170 --> 04:59.674
"First black president of Winchester
goes down in flames."

04:59.757 --> 05:01.801
I'm more disappointed than I am angry.

05:02.468 --> 05:05.138
But you best believe I'm mad as hell, too.

05:06.931 --> 05:07.765
Noted.

05:11.894 --> 05:14.147
-Warmed him up for you.
-Thanks.

05:15.773 --> 05:18.735
[Dean Fairbanks]
Reggie, have a seat, please.

05:24.407 --> 05:26.284
I see you completed all your sessions.

05:26.367 --> 05:27.744
That's good.

05:32.707 --> 05:33.875
Listen.

05:35.460 --> 05:36.753
Brother to brother.

05:38.379 --> 05:39.839
I am here for you

05:39.922 --> 05:42.633
if you ever want to talk
in a less formal setting.

05:43.343 --> 05:45.178
The Met Gala is less formal than this.

05:45.261 --> 05:46.387
[chuckles]

05:47.638 --> 05:49.891
Oh, I gotta run.

05:52.101 --> 05:53.895
Um...

05:53.978 --> 05:55.813
I know you're just doing your job.

05:56.647 --> 06:00.360
Son, my job, basically,

06:01.152 --> 06:03.446
is to approve student events,

06:03.529 --> 06:04.947
glad-hand donors

06:05.031 --> 06:07.367
and try to stay awake
during board meetings.

06:08.451 --> 06:10.369
I'm talking to you from my heart.

06:11.746 --> 06:15.708
We don't always have someone
who understands where we're coming from.

06:17.085 --> 06:20.880
I want you to be in the right head space
so that you can succeed.

06:22.215 --> 06:23.466
Mm-hmm.

06:24.383 --> 06:25.760
[Dean Fairbanks] Listen.

06:25.843 --> 06:28.721
You got 99 problems.
Your head doesn't need to be one.

06:28.805 --> 06:30.765
[chuckles]

06:30.848 --> 06:32.308
I'll think on that.

06:38.898 --> 06:40.983
Hey, what happened to, um...

06:42.318 --> 06:43.778
to Officer Ames?

06:45.947 --> 06:47.949
School's taking appropriate actions.

06:52.286 --> 06:53.121
Right.

07:15.226 --> 07:17.812
[Dereca on TV]  What can you do?
Nothing but come to me.

07:17.895 --> 07:21.315
I understand your need for closure, baby,

07:21.399 --> 07:26.696
but you haven't dealt
with your fire, your rage!

07:27.488 --> 07:29.991
Outside of a snowboarding shop, I mean...

07:30.074 --> 07:31.075
How you doin'?

07:31.784 --> 07:34.537
You know, work, water polo,

07:34.620 --> 07:35.705
steppin' up my needlepoint game--

07:35.788 --> 07:37.290
How are you doing?

07:37.373 --> 07:39.208
I'd be doing much better if people

07:39.292 --> 07:40.960
stopped asking me how I was doing.

07:41.043 --> 07:44.213
Yeah, people care about you
enough to check in.

07:44.297 --> 07:46.174
Sounds fucking awful.

07:47.800 --> 07:50.887
[Dereca]  You were mugged at gunpoint.

07:50.970 --> 07:54.682
You got got! He made you run yo' shit.

07:54.765 --> 07:57.685
Mm-kay? Mm-kay? Mm-kay?

07:58.269 --> 08:00.438
-I can change that.
-Nah.

08:00.521 --> 08:04.066
But it was more than a gun, wasn't it?

08:04.150 --> 08:07.778
It represents something more devastating.

08:08.779 --> 08:12.158
A white man's penis.

08:13.409 --> 08:14.494
Penis!

08:14.577 --> 08:17.497
...stop until...

08:17.955 --> 08:20.458
I feel my tears on my titties.

08:20.541 --> 08:21.751
[Kordell] Sorry, fam.

08:21.834 --> 08:24.128
Our Bible study group reserved the lounge.

08:25.254 --> 08:26.964
Hey, Reggie.

08:27.340 --> 08:29.467
Uh, you know,
maybe you should stick around.

08:29.550 --> 08:32.595
This'll give you more
clarity than "Oh-no-prah," huh?

08:32.678 --> 08:34.805
Is Reggie the only one here?

08:34.889 --> 08:36.891
Oh, sorry, Coco.

08:36.974 --> 08:38.184
Would you like to join?

08:38.267 --> 08:39.685
Not really, no.

08:39.769 --> 08:41.020
